  "response": "Yes, in May 2017, **Financial Management** was a part of the syllabus for **IPCC (Integrated Professional Competence Course) Group 1**, which is now known as **CA Intermediate**. The syllabus for CA exams is revised periodically, and in 2017, Financial Management was indeed one of the subjects in the Group 1 curriculum.\n\n### Key Details:\n- **Subject:** Financial Management\n- **Paper:** Paper 3 (as per the May 2017 syllabus)\n- **Group:** Group 1 of IPCC\n\n### Changes in Syllabus:\nThe CA course syllabus has undergone changes over the years as part of ICAI's (Institute of Chartered Accountants of India) curriculum updates. If you are referring to a specific website that mentions a change in the syllabus, it is likely referring to updates made after May 2017.\n\nFor the latest syllabus, you should always refer to the official ICAI website or the revised study materials provided by ICAI. If you are preparing for a specific exam, ensure you are following the syllabus applicable to your attempt year.",
